 *    b. name: "" (empty string) - should be rejected
 *    c. enabled: null (invalid type  expects boolean)
 *    d. enabled: "yes" (string instead of boolean)
 * 4. For each case, verify that the update is rejected and the API returns a validation error (use TestValidator.error)
 * 5. Finally, attempt a valid update and verify it succeeds for control
 */
